<subSubSection id="2EAE77072F652D5A554AC4E738157D6E" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="DA9819263684CC993BEC7FC29C0C7000" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicName id="768D3DDC63BE39FBD0C244CD83F07914" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1849" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Albux" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Albux</taxonomicName>
J.E. LeConte, 1849: 26 [
<emphasis id="1DCB45D5C703C1A7D02BA67B2AA1FA6A" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">nomen oblitum</emphasis>
, see Bousquet (2008b: 328)]. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="26D96913A4EA716DEBBA4F74276885B6" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis id="BC86189564A8DD8D89F31B0F0E1D8DB5" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Feronia striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828 (= 
<taxonomicName id="C03EBE963F8D0CB87FAA89451CF0245A" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sculptus">
<emphasis id="5BC9EB8A76A51A7C2E6795EE08891F51" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Pterostichus sculptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853) by monotypy. Etymology. Unknown. Note. Hardy et al. (1986: 472) argued that the paper in which this name was proposed was written by John Eatton LeConte and not his son, John Lawrence LeConte.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA43C0CBFA52615050DDA85EB2FA7F1D" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicName id="A8D8AB70B18F0AB50CE4815EE76162CB" authorityName="Leconte" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Abacidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Abacidus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1863b: 9 [
<emphasis id="512A9212DC71DC2DD6D5FED305CB3A5B" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">nomen protectum</emphasis>
]. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="5B09B3EC611BE0A82FED147AC60D20D6" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis id="FE12D5FC005C34009B768C7273CD8485" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Feronia fallax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1828 designated by Casey (1913: 136). Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="205197145B14C4F94FF64DEC240B0FE2" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Abax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C816517C774BCA83702D49C23160572A" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Abax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="30FF326F4F66AB2A9974866D757D48B5" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Latin suffix - 
<emphasis id="FB70D4FC20429572A4D85E494536CEFB" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">idus</emphasis>
(having the nature of), alluding to the superficial resemblance of the adults to those of 
<taxonomicName id="ED68BC97CC49675781317BDA5A6F8AF7" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Abax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3010209C14D18670AC74C5AD53B0ADBD" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Abax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which Dejean originally placed the two species known to LeConte [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B1F0BBC77ADE8CB64B759304AA9764D1" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">
<taxonomicName id="9BF2D447A24D4601B4BB291223B8BCC5" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Peristethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Peristethus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1863b: 9 [junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="5217060F9ED3F75C4B7A9716024E88CA" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Peristethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="86EAE82A8FB72B7A4E8A0365669D43E5" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Peristethus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kaup, 1858]. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="AC606AEC8ACC14B4ACA8E6AAFA1BE3C9" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="permunda">
<emphasis id="A02F579280BAB855A77F0A4D3BA7FCD4" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Feronia permunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830 by monotypy. Synonymy established by Casey (1913: 136). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="6521E43E607226DB5A0487D0569965F6" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">peri</emphasis>
(around, near) and 
<emphasis id="D975EA6920C034D99266CC9C43980A65" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">stethos</emphasis>
(breast, chest) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="299B92639F34264121273498C7CC53C9" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="98542366151D249493375E9F4F0C1833" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E414D75276043E39B0AD0DFA75B70B0" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Five species in the temperate regions of eastern North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5CFA531212AC6A7436380D985A31CB63" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" type="identification">
<paragraph id="D3D7B6174E4AEF9613E03B52345FBFC2" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44A12F19FC2892EBCB1F1262F93FC1FC" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">
Lindroth (1966: 535) provided a key to all species, including also 
<taxonomicName id="C272E80503FF01C27EFBD2093457BDAB" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1873" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesulus">
<emphasis id="6A9595C20AC27ED2492D54F67005B7B6" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Pterostichus obesulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, a species that actually belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="2DC8C8D86B2945DF66BFFE701A54BB28" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Gastrosticta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4682CD2322428BB0BE4CD6F2F59122D5" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Gastrosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sadek (1982) wrote a M.Sc. thesis on the taxonomy of this group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C1D7D22E3DC24CB57B377F5A1041310E" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph id="9AEE28D2F8352C61788C7872EA03EA2B" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="165F12DD172BC2804E9139E450106914" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">
Lindroth (1966: 534), followed recently by Lorenz (2005: 289), treated this group as a distinct genus. Structural characters of the adults and larvae clearly suggest that members of 
<taxonomicName id="B6E4D1AC3075D83CEBFA29981E676597" authorityName="Leconte" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Abacidus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A766A472776B100EACB9387932B7D2FD" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Abacidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are congeneric with those of 
<taxonomicName id="119250C3C560D3ED7FA5B87013A78B89" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22B5D2A8D51C2213BFB0C2818D4C3692" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Pterostichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, the group is probably closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="046F60DBE8DCB394902911EF0E9E2683" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Metallophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCABEB3BA30EA9224D7DEA93CE827641" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Metallophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8CCAA8CAFF09542347A8ADA74EE0982E" authorityName="Megerle &amp; Steven" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Myosodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="521" pageNumber="522" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="223A13631A1573D64029EEB7D3C79008" italics="true" pageId="521" pageNumber="522">Myosodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Bousquet 1999: 148).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
